subSubSection.paragraph:
Holotype
: female, No. CNU-MEC-NN2008228 p/c (Fig. 
3
), preserved in lateral view, thorax partly preserved, abdomen well-preserved, with four wings partly preserved, veins of one forewing mostly discernible, veins of one hind wing relatively discernible. 
Paratypes
: sex unknown, No. CNU-MEC-NN2015026 (Fig. 
4
), preserved in ventral view, thorax and abdomen partly preserved, only right forewing venation clearly discernible; female, CNU-MEC-NN2016020 p/c (Fig. 
5
), body nearly complete but not well-preserved, forewing venation partly discernible.
